    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01989_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Anderton, near Chorley.</name>
                    <name type="place">Lancashire, England<ptr target="loc.04832_n3"/></name>
                    <date when="1892-01-02">2 Jan 92.</date>
                </dateline> 
                <salute>Dear Walt,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Just a few lines to express my constant thought of you and my dearest love. 
                After the suspense of the last two weeks I am heartily glad that the beginning
                of the New Year finds you rallying from your sickness &#38; spared to us once more.<ptr target="loc.02538_n4"/> 
                God bless you &#38; our best love to you.</p>
            <p>Horace<ptr target="n4267"/> kindly sent us a cable message each day during the worst period, &#38; 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01990_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                we at once communicated the news to your chief English friends. 
                I have had letters in return from most of them including Symonds.<ptr target="n0615"/> 
                We are all pleased to know your improved condition.</p>
            <p>I have just received a post card from Carpenter<ptr target="n0141b"/> who is 
                spending a few days in Kent &#38; London. I have heard from him several times lately.</p>
            <p>All going on much as usual here. Yesterday, (New Year's Day) was a perfect day&#8212;the 
                finest I have seen since my retur<supplied reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="high">n</supplied>.</p>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.01991_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
             <p>I write this rather hurriedly. But with love to you &#38; best wishes from 
                 my <choice><orig>inmost</orig><reg>innermost</reg></choice> heart. 
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>I remain always</salute>
                <salute>Yours affectionately</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">JW Wallace</hi></signed> 
            </closer>
